All,

I am sure by now you are aware CardConnect sent out a notice to sever thousand merchants today
indicating they can't process at CU. A large number of those merchants are on the Shift4 platform
and 1 am aware of the impact this had (and could continue to have) on the organization. I assume you
will all be an a conference call first thing tomorrow to discuss.

In any event, 1 just spoke to [REDACTED] the acting General Counsel at CardConnect, I
explained to her that Shift4 was not involved in the notice that went out and if we were consulted we
would have advised them against it due to the large number of impacted merchants.

Shift4 had nothing to do with the noticc.

As to the root cause, my understanding is that there are ongoing negotiations between CU and
CardConnect. It appears CU is attempting to implement fees that are excessive, not based on
market rates, and inconsistent with the negotiated agreement between CU and CardConnect.

I made it clear to [REDACTED] that CardConnect should resolve the issue with CU as quickly as
possible for the sake of the many impacted merchants.

This is where things stand at the moment I will keep you informed I will be around all day,
